			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The ARM validator, by design, generalizes instructions into &amp;quot;instruction 
classes.&amp;quot;  The classification is not always precise, but I try to err on the 
side of banning safe instructions, rather than allowing unsafe ones (for 
obvious reasons).

For a variety of reasons, there are some instructions that we refuse to 
allow in untrusted code, but which are nonetheless safe in our SFI model.  
If an instruction isn't generated in the wild by our toolchain, please add 
it here and we'll refine the validator model as time allows.  (If it's 
blocking the toolchain, file a separate higher-priority bug.)</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-15T19:05:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-03-02T22:35:48.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Assigned</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
